snippet.textDisplay: After some time to reflect, yesterday was so poor and further enforcing some opinions I think most of us have had regardless of some of the great wins we had recently. Aurier is not good enough, Gazzaniga is not a premier league goalkeeper and that the formation we use DOES NOT work. It is too negative, it tells the other team we fear you and that our defence is potentially fragile. Putting a more attacking formation gives us the chance to score more than them ASAP and then put defensive players on. Dier is terrible, I am sorry to say this as I like him but all of the time he was playing in front of my very eyes yesterday he was walking around, not marking anyone and passing the ball to chelsea half the time. NDombele, Sessengnon and Lo Celso should be starting, remove the two defensive midfield options and just have the one. Get all our goals and attacking done, then switch to defensive. I am tired of this season watching negative football and the mentality. Is it because we simply do not have good enough players to switch the formation? Who knows other than Jose really, but as someone who has gone to majority of games I am going by what I witness too often this season.
